cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO

The paper discusses the study of one-way functions in cryptography, which is a topic closely related to computer security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions algebraic properties of one-way functions, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of one-way functions in protocols and digital signatures suggests that it may also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
